{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MX6TeZ6RoW89eYd8qQ8FG4","type":"tool_result","content":"320\t\n321\t### Manual verification\n322\t\n323\t- [ ] T-000008: Run the smoke test by hand\n324\t\n325\t## Bugs\n326\t\n327\t- [ ] T-000009: Crash on empty PLAN.md\n328\t```\n329\t\n330\t### 4.2 Productions\n331\t\n332\t```\n333\tPlan        ← Magic Preamble? PhaseOrBugs+ EOF\n334\tMagic       ← \"<!--\" WS? \"bob-plan-format:\" WS? Int WS? \"-->\" NL\n335\tPreamble    ← H1 NL Prose?\n336\tPhaseOrBugs ← Phase / BugsSection\n337\tPhase       ← PhaseHead PhaseIdComment? Prose? Subsection* Item+\n338\tPhaseHead   ← \"##\" WS (\"Stage\" / \"Phase\") WS Int \":\" WS Text NL\n339\tPhaseIdComment ← \"<!--\" WS? \"phase_id:\" WS? Word WS? \"-->\" NL\n340\tSubsection  ← \"###\" WS Text NL Prose?\n341\tBugsSection ← \"##\" WS \"Bugs\" NL Item*\n342\tItem        ← Indent* \"-\" WS \"[\" Status \"]\" WS TaskId Tag* Text Annot* NL DepsLine? Item* RuledOut*\n343\tStatus      ← \" \" / \"x\" / \"X\" / \"!\"\n344\tTaskId      ← TaskRef \":\" WS                      ; the colon-suffixed form used as a task's own ID\n345\tTaskRef     ← \"T-\" Digit+                         ; the bare form used to reference another task\n346\tTag         ← FlagTag / ActionTag                 ; leading position only (§4.3)\n347\tFlagTag     ← \"[\" (\"USER\" / \"BATCH\") \"]\" WS\n348\tActionTag   ← \"[AUTO:\" Word \"]\" WS Text?          ; args are remainder of text\n349\tAnnot       ← WS \"[\" Key \":\" WS Value \"]\"         ; e.g. [feat: \"...\"], [fix: \"...\"]\n350\tDepsLine    ← Indent* \"@deps\" (WS TaskRef)+ NL    ; bare IDs, no trailing colon\n351\tRuledOut    ← Indent* \"[RULEDOUT]\" WS Text NL\n352\tIndent      ← (WS WS)+                            ; numeric nesting, 2-space canonical\n353\tProse       ← (! Item ! PhaseHead ! Subsection . )* NL\n354\t```\n355\t\n356\tNotes on the grammar:\n357\t\n358\t- Indentation is significant for nesting but **numeric**, not fixed.\n359\t  A child task requires strictly greater indent than its parent.\n360\t  The canonical renderer emits two-space units; the parser accepts\n361\t  any consistent unit ≥ 1 space. (Duplo's PLAN.md uses 2; McLoop's\n362\t  uses 3; PLAN.EXAMPLE.md uses 2.)\n363\t- Unknown bracket tags are rejected by validation, not silently\n364\t  ignored. New tags require a library change.\n365\t- Prose is allowed in three places: preamble after H1, phase prose\n366\t  after a phase heading, and subsection prose after a `###`\n367\t  heading. Loose checklist items inside Prose are syntax errors.\n368\t- The `<!-- bob-plan-format: 1 -->` magic line is recommended but\n369\t  optional during migration; its absence triggers compatibility\n370\t  mode (see §8).\n371\t\n372\t### 4.3 Tag families\n373\t\n374\tThree families. Position rules are stricter than McLoop's current\n375\tsubstring-matching behavior: operational tags are recognized **only\n376\tin the leading position** of a task line, immediately after the\n377\tcheckbox and task ID. This is a deliberate departure from McLoop,\n378\twhich classifies any task whose text contains `[USER]` anywhere as\n379\ta USER task. A task description that references the tag form in\n380\tprose (in quoted code, in example text, in references to the syntax\n381\titself) is not classified as that operational kind.\n382\t\n383\t1. **Flag tags** (`[USER]`, `[BATCH]`): must appear immediately\n384\t   after the checkbox and task ID, before the task description.\n385\t   `[USER]` or `[BATCH]` appearing later in the text is prose, not\n386\t   a tag.\n387\t2. **Action tags** (`[AUTO:<action>] <args>`): must appear\n388\t   immediately after the flag tags (if any) and before the task\n389\t   description. The argument string is the text from the closing\n390\t   bracket of the action tag to end of line. `[AUTO:...]` tokens\n391\t   appearing later in the text are prose.\n392\t3. **Key-value annotations** (`[feat: \"...\"]`, `[fix: \"...\"]`): at\n393\t   end of line. Multiple allowed.\n394\t\n395\tCompatibility mode parses leading tags as tags and treats non-leading\n396\tbracketed tokens that resemble flag or action tags as prose. The\n397\tparser may emit a validation warning when a non-leading token like\n398\t`[USER]` appears inside task text — the warning is opt-in; the\n399\tdefault is silent acceptance as prose."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8967cf94-692c-42c2-9412-97ac73ed5641","uuid":"a440269a-53f8-4d4a-9a2e-27e23160c78d","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:05:56.669Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/mhcoen/proj/bob/design/planfile.md","content":"\n### Manual verification\n\n- [ ] T-000008: Run the smoke test by hand\n\n## Bugs\n\n- [ ] T-000009: Crash on empty PLAN.md\n```\n\n### 4.2 Productions\n\n```\nPlan        ← Magic Preamble? PhaseOrBugs+ EOF\nMagic       ← \"<!--\" WS? \"bob-plan-format:\" WS? Int WS? \"-->\" NL\nPreamble    ← H1 NL Prose?\nPhaseOrBugs ← Phase / BugsSection\nPhase       ← PhaseHead PhaseIdComment? Prose? Subsection* Item+\nPhaseHead   ← \"##\" WS (\"Stage\" / \"Phase\") WS Int \":\" WS Text NL\nPhaseIdComment ← \"<!--\" WS? \"phase_id:\" WS? Word WS? \"-->\" NL\nSubsection  ← \"###\" WS Text NL Prose?\nBugsSection ← \"##\" WS \"Bugs\" NL Item*\nItem        ← Indent* \"-\" WS \"[\" Status \"]\" WS TaskId Tag* Text Annot* NL DepsLine? Item* RuledOut*\nStatus      ← \" \" / \"x\" / \"X\" / \"!\"\nTaskId      ← TaskRef \":\" WS                      ; the colon-suffixed form used as a task's own ID\nTaskRef     ← \"T-\" Digit+                         ; the bare form used to reference another task\nTag         ← FlagTag / ActionTag                 ; leading position only (§4.3)\nFlagTag     ← \"[\" (\"USER\" / \"BATCH\") \"]\" WS\nActionTag   ← \"[AUTO:\" Word \"]\" WS Text?          ; args are remainder of text\nAnnot       ← WS \"[\" Key \":\" WS Value \"]\"         ; e.g. [feat: \"...\"], [fix: \"...\"]\nDepsLine    ← Indent* \"@deps\" (WS TaskRef)+ NL    ; bare IDs, no trailing colon\nRuledOut    ← Indent* \"[RULEDOUT]\" WS Text NL\nIndent      ← (WS WS)+                            ; numeric nesting, 2-space canonical\nProse       ← (! Item ! PhaseHead ! Subsection . )* NL\n```\n\nNotes on the grammar:\n\n- Indentation is significant for nesting but **numeric**, not fixed.\n  A child task requires strictly greater indent than its parent.\n  The canonical renderer emits two-space units; the parser accepts\n  any consistent unit ≥ 1 space. (Duplo's PLAN.md uses 2; McLoop's\n  uses 3; PLAN.EXAMPLE.md uses 2.)\n- Unknown bracket tags are rejected by validation, not silently\n  ignored. New tags require a library change.\n- Prose is allowed in three places: preamble after H1, phase prose\n  after a phase heading, and subsection prose after a `###`\n  heading. Loose checklist items inside Prose are syntax errors.\n- The `<!-- bob-plan-format: 1 -->` magic line is recommended but\n  optional during migration; its absence triggers compatibility\n  mode (see §8).\n\n### 4.3 Tag families\n\nThree families. Position rules are stricter than McLoop's current\nsubstring-matching behavior: operational tags are recognized **only\nin the leading position** of a task line, immediately after the\ncheckbox and task ID. This is a deliberate departure from McLoop,\nwhich classifies any task whose text contains `[USER]` anywhere as\na USER task. A task description that references the tag form in\nprose (in quoted code, in example text, in references to the syntax\nitself) is not classified as that operational kind.\n\n1. **Flag tags** (`[USER]`, `[BATCH]`): must appear immediately\n   after the checkbox and task ID, before the task description.\n   `[USER]` or `[BATCH]` appearing later in the text is prose, not\n   a tag.\n2. **Action tags** (`[AUTO:<action>] <args>`): must appear\n   immediately after the flag tags (if any) and before the task\n   description. The argument string is the text from the closing\n   bracket of the action tag to end of line. `[AUTO:...]` tokens\n   appearing later in the text are prose.\n3. **Key-value annotations** (`[feat: \"...\"]`, `[fix: \"...\"]`): at\n   end of line. Multiple allowed.\n\nCompatibility mode parses leading tags as tags and treats non-leading\nbracketed tokens that resemble flag or action tags as prose. The\nparser may emit a validation warning when a non-leading token like\n`[USER]` appears inside task text — the warning is opt-in; the\ndefault is silent acceptance as prose.","numLines":80,"startLine":320,"totalLines":755}}}
