{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NJPfEMNKFbJLzDs9ptm39s","type":"tool_result","content":"612\t## 8. Migration\n613\t\n614\tPhased migration. No big-bang rewrite.\n615\t\n616\t### Phase A: parser-only\n617\t\n618\t1. Add `bob_tools.planfile` with the parser, renderer, validator,\n619\t   and migrator. Parser accepts both old (no IDs, headings without\n620\t   phase-id comments) and new (with IDs and comments) forms.\n621\t   Renderer emits canonical form. `migrate(plan)` is a separate\n622\t   operation that assigns missing IDs and phase-id comments.\n623\t2. `@deps` is supported from the start. The parser reads `@deps`\n624\t   lines, the renderer writes them, validation requires referenced\n625\t   IDs to exist in the plan, and `next_tasks` honors deps when\n626\t   deciding actionability. Minimal scope: dependency graph cycle\n627\t   detection is *not* required in Phase A (a cycle just blocks\n628\t   `next_tasks` from progressing past it; callers detect that as\n629\t   no actionable task remaining).\n630\t3. Add `bob-plan validate PLAN.md` and `bob-plan fmt PLAN.md`\n631\t   commands. `fmt` calls `parse_plan`, then `migrate`, then\n632\t   `save`. Idempotent.\n633\t4. McLoop and Duplo continue to use their existing parsers during\n634\t   Phase A.\n635\t\n636\t### Phase B: McLoop migration\n637\t\n638\t1. McLoop's settle hook calls `planfile.resolve_task_context`\n639\t   instead of `ledger_emit.find_explicit_phase_id_for_task`.\n640\t   `resolve_phase_id` becomes a shim.\n641\t2. `mcloop.checklist.parse` delegates to `planfile.parse_plan`.\n642\t   `check_off`, `mark_failed`, `find_next` delegate to\n643\t   `planfile.complete_task`, `fail_task`, `next_tasks`.\n644\t3. McLoop's parser disappears or remains as a 5-line shim.\n645\t\n646\t### Phase C: Duplo migration\n647\t\n648\t1. Duplo's planner stops emitting raw Markdown. It produces typed\n649\t   `Plan` objects (via LLM-proposed task text, but with structure\n650\t   assigned by Duplo). Duplo calls `planfile.render_plan` to write.\n651\t2. LLM output is validated by `planfile.validate_plan` before\n652\t   write. Malformed output is rejected; Duplo retries or fails the\n653\t   phase. The LLM never owns plan structure.\n654\t3. Duplo annotations (`[feat: \"...\"]`, `[fix: \"...\"]`) are\n655\t   first-class in the typed `Plan` (fields on `Task`), not parsed\n656\t   from text.\n657\t\n658\t### Phase D: cleanup\n659\t\n660\t1. Delete `mcloop.checklist` if the shim has no remaining callers.\n661\t2. Decide whether `commit_landed` should gain `attributed_task_id`.\n662\t   If yes, that is a ledger schema bump, not a planfile change.\n663\t\n664\t## 9. What changes for humans\n665\t\n666\tHumans can still hand-edit PLAN.md. Constraints:\n667\t\n668\t- Editing task text is safe.\n669\t- Editing checkboxes is safe; the consistency check will surface\n670\t  divergence from the ledger on the next run, but does not auto-\n671\t  rewrite."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8967cf94-692c-42c2-9412-97ac73ed5641","uuid":"5f79efe5-bc90-48f2-8d79-61ba620ba8d1","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:06:08.679Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/mhcoen/proj/bob/design/planfile.md","content":"## 8. Migration\n\nPhased migration. No big-bang rewrite.\n\n### Phase A: parser-only\n\n1. Add `bob_tools.planfile` with the parser, renderer, validator,\n   and migrator. Parser accepts both old (no IDs, headings without\n   phase-id comments) and new (with IDs and comments) forms.\n   Renderer emits canonical form. `migrate(plan)` is a separate\n   operation that assigns missing IDs and phase-id comments.\n2. `@deps` is supported from the start. The parser reads `@deps`\n   lines, the renderer writes them, validation requires referenced\n   IDs to exist in the plan, and `next_tasks` honors deps when\n   deciding actionability. Minimal scope: dependency graph cycle\n   detection is *not* required in Phase A (a cycle just blocks\n   `next_tasks` from progressing past it; callers detect that as\n   no actionable task remaining).\n3. Add `bob-plan validate PLAN.md` and `bob-plan fmt PLAN.md`\n   commands. `fmt` calls `parse_plan`, then `migrate`, then\n   `save`. Idempotent.\n4. McLoop and Duplo continue to use their existing parsers during\n   Phase A.\n\n### Phase B: McLoop migration\n\n1. McLoop's settle hook calls `planfile.resolve_task_context`\n   instead of `ledger_emit.find_explicit_phase_id_for_task`.\n   `resolve_phase_id` becomes a shim.\n2. `mcloop.checklist.parse` delegates to `planfile.parse_plan`.\n   `check_off`, `mark_failed`, `find_next` delegate to\n   `planfile.complete_task`, `fail_task`, `next_tasks`.\n3. McLoop's parser disappears or remains as a 5-line shim.\n\n### Phase C: Duplo migration\n\n1. Duplo's planner stops emitting raw Markdown. It produces typed\n   `Plan` objects (via LLM-proposed task text, but with structure\n   assigned by Duplo). Duplo calls `planfile.render_plan` to write.\n2. LLM output is validated by `planfile.validate_plan` before\n   write. Malformed output is rejected; Duplo retries or fails the\n   phase. The LLM never owns plan structure.\n3. Duplo annotations (`[feat: \"...\"]`, `[fix: \"...\"]`) are\n   first-class in the typed `Plan` (fields on `Task`), not parsed\n   from text.\n\n### Phase D: cleanup\n\n1. Delete `mcloop.checklist` if the shim has no remaining callers.\n2. Decide whether `commit_landed` should gain `attributed_task_id`.\n   If yes, that is a ledger schema bump, not a planfile change.\n\n## 9. What changes for humans\n\nHumans can still hand-edit PLAN.md. Constraints:\n\n- Editing task text is safe.\n- Editing checkboxes is safe; the consistency check will surface\n  divergence from the ledger on the next run, but does not auto-\n  rewrite.","numLines":60,"startLine":612,"totalLines":755}}}
